nd marketed the liberalism of their moment-and ours.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 23. Jul 2020) 0aAfrican Americans in literature. 0aAmerican fictiony20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aLiberalism in literature. 0aPolitics and literaturezUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aPopular culture in literature. 0aRace in literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080478261640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804782616423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804782616.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles